article_title: Greek Election Likely to Have Muted Effect on Markets
article_text:
As Greece went to the polls Sunday, investors were bracing for a volatile reaction in markets. But some analysts say the wider impact is likely to be contained.

The results of the vote are all-important for the future of Greece, but their broader effects will be cushioned both by Greece’s isolation from the euro-zone financial system and by the...
